##How Ali dealt with SARS 17 years ago

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Savio at Lakeside University

Seventeen years ago, when Alibaba, then a "small and medium-sized enterprise, " was hit by SARS, all employees at the headquarters were placed in mandatory isolation for two weeks. Savio was the COO at the time, a witness to the incident and a decision-maker.

As the epidemic continues, entrepreneurs are taking on social responsibility to support the front line, but they are also beginning to think rationally about what to do about it. Mind and pattern is from the difficulties and trauma out of the exercise, in the face of disaster, to survive, is a victory.

How does the company respond to sudden crises?
What should the leadership do when crisis strikes?
What is the basic motivation that sustains a team to overcome difficulties?
At this time, the CEO to what kind of mentality to face the challenge?
……

With these questions in mind, we interviewed Mr. Guan Mingsheng. Here is his dictation.

As the epidemic continues, entrepreneurs are taking on social responsibility to support the front line, but they are also beginning to think rationally about what to do about it. What is the basic motivation that sustains a team to overcome difficulties?

……

With these questions in mind, we interviewed Mr. Guan Mingsheng. Here is his dictation.

01

That they may be "quarantined. "

What have we done to prepare

At the beginning of 2003, Alibaba was still small, with hundreds of headquarters in Hangzhou and more than 10 offices across the country.

In early May, a colleague, Song Jie, came down with a cold and fever after returning to Hangzhou from Guangzhou, and everyone started to get nervous. At that time there were one or two suspected cases of "SARS" in Hangzhou, have been quarantined to the hospital.

If Song Jie is quarantined, what about Ali's hundreds in Hangzhou?

There was a lot of uncertainty over the last few days. The company made contingency plans in advance. Jack Ma, Peng Lei and others actively communicated with the government. Wu Ma (Wu Yongming) , Lion (Shi Yufeng) and others in charge of technology adjusted the company's wiring to prepare for future isolation if it is really necessary, can ensure that all people can be normal to answer the phone, Internet.

There was a very special thing that happened, a lot of students came up to me and said, Savio, I want $2,000. I said, what do you need $2,000 for? He said I already had a computer, $2,000 for broadband, and if I was quarantined, I could work from home. I said yes. I gave him $2,000. He wrote me a note.

One after another, many students came to get money from me during that time. I gave them all. I remember sending out more than 300,000 RMB. At that time, it was a lot of money.

It was the "May Day" holiday, I returned to Hong Kong the same day, received a phone call that Song Jie as a "suspected case" was sent to designated hospitals isolation, Hangzhou all staff back home self-isolation. Within a few hours, everyone took the money and went shopping, brought home their computers, pulled out the wire, bought their desks and groceries, and prepared to go back to work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The process is spontaneous, it doesn't take management to say what you're going to do, everybody automatically says I'm going to do this, I'm going to do that. The company contacted the Telecom Department and sent out technical support students to ensure that every colleague's home could be connected to the Internet and the company's system.

I was quarantined in my home in Hong Kong. I told my wife it was a big deal, so we wrote our will. I remember writing a letter to my daughter, telling her where things were at home.

02

What was management doing

Why, many ask, were Ali's employees so effective at responding?

In my opinion, the most important thing is the company's cultural values. The employees were incredibly united and incredibly spontaneous.

To deal with sudden external disasters, these two things are the most important, one is unity, two is spontaneous.

Everyone knows what the priorities are based on? I heard it more than once, and they all said, we can be locked up, but the customer service can not be interrupted. This is Ali's "customers first" cultural values. If this culture hadn't done it long ago, you'd only be able to give orders in times of crisis. One of the great advantages of Ali at the time was that he didn't have to do anything.

So after the quarantine, what's our management doing?

I remember Jack Ma calling the isolation hospital every day, begging them not to lock her up with the other two patients. Because in his mind, Song Jie should be fine, but if the patients are locked together, things are more complicated. Therefore, he was very determined to call the hospital every day to do this work.

He said to me, "Savio, if something does happen, how am I going to give this little girl to her mother? "

What am I GONNA do? Peng Lei gave me the phone numbers of all the employees. I am at home in Hong Kong, a landline, two mobile phones, every day to call hundreds of students to say: Hello, I am Savio, how is the situation and so on. They said, we can do this, we can do this.

This is what I can do, at this time, can not command, can not supervise, this time must give everyone encouragement, give everyone refueling!

At that time, everyone was isolated in their living quarters, three meals a day were delivered by someone else, and there was a lock on the outside to lock up the people inside. Locked-up people, some with parents, some with couples, some with co-workers, it's a very special situation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The isolated city of Hangzhou is Alibaba's headquarters and has more than a dozen field offices, mainly for sales students. Headquarters functions can not be paralyzed, otherwise the entire company will not be able to function.

I call to Hangzhou any of the home of a classmate, are angelic voice: "Ali Baba, hello" . If I were a client, I wouldn't even know the company was locked up. Everyone is full of life, just like working in a company.

Students in Hangzhou, isolation at home is also very boring. They continued their work through instant messaging, email and phone calls during the day, and in the evening, there was an online karaoke singing contest. These are all good ways to make the best of a bad situation, to relax people, to boost morale, and that's the key.

03

Wasn't an opportunity at the time

Is a huge challenge

A lot of people said SARS was an opportunity for Ali, but it was a huge challenge.

Faced with such a disaster, many enterprises could only choose to have a holiday. At that time, the psychological pressure of the employees was also very great. They could totally say that I was already very sad. You still want me to answer the phone, and you also want me to help clients solve problems, and you have a sales call to make, so save it!

But no one said that. No one was left behind. Incredible unity, incredible spontaneity. I thought, without the insistence of the students, these so-called "chance" of things are equal to zero.

Because "SARS" impact, no business owners are willing to meet and trade, our site traffic instantly increased 7 times, technology students to do the most important thing to ensure that can not be down. The volume of business has greatly increased, which means that the students have to work more than normal times, it is simply overwhelmed.

After the quarantine ended, by June 1, one of our departments, the telemarketing department, had made one million sales. The telemarketers were selling at 2,300 yuan per call, and about two out of every 100 calls were successful. It took ten thousand calls to get to one million, and they put in more effort than usual.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
One day I called a female classmate, the other end of the phone is a bit heavy bass, "Ali Baba, hello. ". I said, who are you? He said, sir, is there something wrong with you, and if it is, I can help you with it. I said to him, I'm Savio. Savio, he said, my daughter and her mother are online in front of us, solving a problem for another client, and I'm answering her phone. So this is dad. He's figured out our business process!

So it wasn't SARS that brought about the opportunity, it was we who turned the disaster into a driving force. Because the team is so together, so united, so aware of what needs to be done, and they're doing it on their own. Because in this situation, management can't tell him what to do. All we can do is care, encourage and call them every day.

After two weeks of isolation, I returned to Hangzhou just in time for Song Jie's release. That Day, I, Jack Ma and Mrs. Jack Ma went to the hospital to pick up Song Jie, and the four of US cried. That's something you never forget.

Why are you crying? It's because I'm relieved that Song Jie is OK, we're all OK. The most important thing is that Song Jie is OK, and Jack Ma is relieved, because he can send Song Jie's mother and father's daughter back.

04

The CEO must be calm in the face of danger

Encountered similar "SARS" , "new crown" such a sudden crisis, affecting the normal operation of the company, each company to deal with the situation is different, temporary emergency measures of course important, if not chaos.

But I think the most important thing is the basic skills, that is, the construction of cultural values in peacetime, is the mission and vision that we all agree on. Only in this way can we ensure firm unity and cohesion, and unity will not be afraid.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Alibaba has been doing cultural values since 2001, the first quarter of March 2001 began to include values in the performance appraisal, this is incredible. There have been 2001,2002 more than two years of impact, a variety of cases, we are in a good mood, the first response to a crisis is the customer first -- "We may be locked up, but, the customer service can not be interrupted. "

With unity of purpose, there is cohesion, unity, and clarity of purpose. No one asked what I should do at this time, there are customers to support customers, people in the background to help them support customers, service can not be interrupted, the machine can not be down, all people are doing their own work.

Like the encounter of this "new crown" epidemic, the CEO must not be anxious, must be calm, calm, to be very clear.

When the CEO's in a mess, the company's in a mess!

CEO can not do too much, must pick the most important things to do, each company's most important things are not the same, in the final analysis is how the business continues, cash flow, supply chain is not broken.

The other one, whatever it takes, is to bring people together. Be Sure to support and encourage your employees to spend where they need to spend their money and get through this time. This is the time to test everyone's basic skills.

05

There are three things you need to do to get started

Cultural values are paramount

Before long we'll be on the ground, and I suggest three things for a CEO to do:

First, look for weaknesses in a company during a crisis.

Can the team withstand the pressure, can quickly restore business, insufficient local organization what resources and manpower to do improvement. This crisis is a severe stress test for small and medium-sized enterprises.

When you start work, make it clear to your colleagues that you're doing a good job under this kind of pressure, but on the other hand you can see that we have some holes. To make a serious summary, to give everyone a very clear direction, so that everyone back on the road.

Second, after this crisis, think about the longer term.

Is the company's basic business model resistant to repression? If not, what needs to change? The big question is, what's my business model?

Many small business owners are basically doing while making money, but a lot of time did not ask me what is the business model. Because they are busy, they struggle everyday, they worry about all kinds of things every day. They haven't sat down properly to think about this question. Now, if they have some time, they need to sit down and ask this question, what customer needs did I solve? Could this model be solved online?

Finally, we should emphasize that we must attach importance to cultural values.

Cultural values are a company's main strength, but also the strength that can be cultivated slowly. But when it comes to a major disaster, this thing can come in handy, and the company stays together. This is something you have to start thinking about and doing.

Cultural values are forged from real shared experiences. "SARS" after the first World War also precipitation as a part of Ali culture, held on May 10 every year, Ali Day activities, inviting the family members of employees to get together, is to commemorate the experience and spirit of this joint battle.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In fact, every company has cultural values, for small and medium-sized enterprises, in fact, is the boss of the cultural values. Ali's cultural values were shaped by the experiences of Jack Ma and his 18 arhats, not my culture, which many people mistakenly believed Savio had brought to Alibaba. Culture already exists, and what we did then was take seven hours to filter it out, extract it, and let the past sink in.

It took Peng Lei and his colleagues three months to write down the first version of the "nine swords of solitude" act, which was crucial. Write down all of these specific actions, and you'll have a handle.

If the boss doesn't do this, he doesn't know what his goal is. If his goal and mission is to make money, then there's already a problem. Then his employees are his money making tools, and they can't be kept.

Many small business owners don't understand this, thinking that mission vision values were developed with the help of a consulting firm. Many say that Ali's cultural values are good, that Ali embraces change, and that we embrace change, ali has customers first, we have customers first and so on. But it's not their own, because they're not turning it into a behavior, and that's a big problem.

So, every SME boss has to ask, what is my mission? Am I offering something in this business that no one else is offering. If he doesn't get it, how can he get his employees to understand what one thing they are focused on doing, what two things are, and what three things are.

After this event, the boss to really do solid cultural values, to think about how to put the long-term interests of employees and the long-term interests of the company together. The most important thing is to do well in the internal power, because for a thousand days, training internal power is the same, long-term training internal power, your immunity will be improved.

* From the University of Lakeside
